<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <head>250. Telegram 796 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d250fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/9–2855. Secret.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-28">September 28, 1955, 10
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d250-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d250-1"/>
                        <p>796. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Department’s unnumbered Niact September 28 correcting text Deptel 798 not
                            received until 5 p.m. Geneva time. As will be seen from report today’s
                            meeting (Mytel 795, paragraph 6) I used phraseology “accounting for US
                            personnel.” Although I was bothered by omission of “military”, there was
                            no time for confirmation. Believe I was successful in skirting around
                            subject and I can pick up matter at next meeting.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>